                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14088030" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 6 Aug 2014 18:51:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what&apos;s going on here, because the log in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7706&quot; title=&quot;CompactionExecutor Error: CompactionInterruptedException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7706&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7706&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; clearly shows some interruptions being (correctly) logged at info and debug, but others at error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CompactionExecutor attempts to deal with CIE as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;I think we have two problems.

CompactionTask assumes it will be run on a CompactionExecutor, which handles CIE as follows:

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;        // modified from DebuggableThreadPoolExecutor so that CompactionInterruptedExceptions are not logged&lt;br/&gt;
        @Override&lt;br/&gt;
        public void afterExecute(Runnable r, Throwable t)&lt;br/&gt;
        {&lt;br/&gt;
            super.afterExecute(r, t);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (t == null)&lt;br/&gt;
                t = DebuggableThreadPoolExecutor.extractThrowable(r);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (t != null)&lt;br/&gt;
            {&lt;br/&gt;
                if (t instanceof CompactionInterruptedException)&lt;/p&gt;
                {
                    logger.info(t.getMessage());
                    logger.debug(&quot;Full interruption stack trace:&quot;, t);
                }
&lt;p&gt;                else&lt;/p&gt;
                {
                    DebuggableThreadPoolExecutor.handleOrLog(t);
                }
&lt;p&gt;            }&lt;br/&gt;
        }&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mshuler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mshuler&quot;&gt;mshuler&lt;/a&gt; can reproduce with the split test, what does it bisect to?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14088925" author="krummas" created="Thu, 7 Aug 2014 07:06:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the exception gets logged as ERROR since we call super.afterExecute first in CE.afterExecute&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;attaching patch to remove the super call&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14089255" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 7 Aug 2014 14:26:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
